For the first $\#N$:
\begin{align*}
\#58 &= .5(58) + 1 \\
&= 29 + 1 \\
&= 30
\end{align*}

Next,
\begin{align*}
\#30 &= .5(30) + 1 \\
&= 15 + 1 \\
&= 16
\end{align*}

Finally,
\begin{align*}
\#16 &= .5(16) + 1 \\
&= 8 + 1 \\
&= 9
\end{align*}

Therefore, $\#(\#(\#58)) = 9$.

